RenderDef (GUI item type)
=========================

Much like windowDef, but it can contain a 3D model (in the [LWO](LWO\_(file\_format)) format).

Additional properties
---------------------

-   [model](Model\_(GUI\_item\_property))
-   animClass
-   anim
-   [model](Model\_(GUI\_item\_property))
-   [modelRotate](ModelRotate\_(GUI\_item\_property))
-   [modelOrigin](ModelOrigin\_(GUI\_item\_property))
-   [needsRender](NeedsRender\_(GUI\_item\_property))
-   [viewOffset](ViewOffset\_(GUI\_item\_property))
-   [lightOrigin](LightOrigin\_(GUI\_item\_property))
-   [lightColor](LightColor\_(GUI\_item\_property))

Example(s)
----------

`renderDef MarsRender {`
`   rect        0, 20, 640, 430`
`   visible     1`
`   backcolor   0, 0, 0, 0.4`
`   model       "models/wipes/planet2.lwo"`
`   needsRender     1`
`   modelRotate     0, time * 0.001, 0, 0`
`   modelOrigin     -80, 0, -25, 0`
`   viewOffset  -300, -28, 0, 0`
`   lightOrigin     0, 0, 0, 0`
`   lightColor  1, 1, 1, 1`
`   notime      1`
`   definevec4  "$marsRotate"   0, time * 0.001, 0, 0`
`   float starmove  0`
`}`

